                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 European War 1939/733: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Beirut</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Beirut</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-06-20T23:00:00+02:00"
                            >June 20, 1941—11 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 20—6:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>232. For Secretary and Under Secretary. Your 105 [<hi rend="italic">104</hi>],
                    June 19. Please inform British Embassy that in view of certain developments in
                    the local situation I would suggest confining ourselves for the moment to
                    communicating informally to Conty only paragraphs 1 and 2 and perhaps substance
                    of subheadings 1, 2, 5 and 6 under paragraph 3. That is really about all he
                    asked for and the rest we can tell him as soon as French authorities have
                    definitely decided to discuss terms.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
